{
  "doc_id": "10429",
  "text": "Two other large series of 35 patients [CITATION_1] and 24 patients [CITATION_2] are in the literature. Our findings regarding the significance of prior trauma to later presentation with os odontoideum are opposite to those of Fielding et al. (6% vs 49%) [CITATION_3] . Most of the cases in their series gave a general history of prior trauma. In only four of 17 was the trauma specifically to the head or neck. Furthermore, the series was obtained before CT was available. The diagnosis was made exclusively on plain radiographs. It is possible, therefore, that some of their cases might actually have been fracture non-unions.",
